The paper discusses the use of deep architectures in machine learning, specifically Deep Belief Networks (DBNs) which are commonly used in the sub-field of deep learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of Restricted Boltzmann Machines (RBMs) which are a type of neural network used in unsupervised learning (cs.NE). The paper presents an improvement in a common method used in training RBMs, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments conducted in the paper involve image classification tasks using the MNIST dataset (cs.CV) and letter classification using the ISOLET dataset (cs.CL).
